Bolivia â€™s mining exports revenue
jumped 42 percent to a record last year on surging metals
prices,  Los Tiempos  reported.  Mining exports rose to $3.4 billion from $2.4 billion in
2010, the newspaper said, citing Mining Minister Jose Pimentel.
The mining industry paid $164 million in royalties and $272
million in taxes last year, according to Cochabamba, Bolivia-
based Los Tiempos.  Bolivia produced about 7 metric tons of gold last year, the
